// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// FILE STRUCTURE — three libraries.
//
//   1. EXERCISE_LIBRARY_META, EXERCISE_LIBRARY, PROGRESSION_GROUPS
//      The exercise reference data. Each exercise: id, name, category,
//      equipment, muscles[], type, advanced, progressionGroup/
//      progressionLevel, supportsAssist, supportsWeight, supportsLevel,
//      style, notes.
//        supportsLevel: true if difficulty can be regressed/progressed via
//        support (knees down, band/chair assist, elevation) without
//        changing the movement — these exercises can carry a levelModifier
//        when logged. Weighted barbell/kettlebell lifts are always false;
//        their load is entered live in the app and is never stored here.
//        style: 'strength' | 'mobility' | 'hiit' | 'cardio'.
//        unilateral: true if reps/hold-time for this exercise are counted
//        per side (e.g. one-arm push-up, pistol squat). Used to relabel the
//        reps field to "reps (each side)" / "seconds (each side)" in the
//        live level UI. Independent of supportsLevel.
//
//      PROGRESSION_GROUPS: each level object also carries a `threshold`
//      (number) + `thresholdUnit` ('reps' | 'seconds') and `unilateral`
//      flag, used by the live skill-ladder mechanism's auto-advance check —
//      meet or beat a level's threshold and the stored level for that chain
//      bumps up by one. See workout.js: getSkillLevel / setSkillLevel /
//      resolveSkillEntry.
//
//   2. WORKOUTS
//      Standalone, reusable workouts, each with an ordered `entries` list.
//      Entry types:
//        'set'     — exerciseId, levelModifier (only if supportsLevel),
//                    weightKg (only if supportsWeight and a fixed load
//                    applies), reps, sets, restSeconds, sideNote.
//        'pyramid' — exerciseId, capMinutes, restBetweenPyramids. Peak
//                    reps are discovered live, so no fixed rows exist.
//        'skill'   — progressionGroup, label, sets, restSeconds,
//                    restAfterExercise, sideNote. No exerciseId/reps —
//                    resolveSkillEntry() in workout.js looks up the
//                    person's current level in that PROGRESSION_GROUPS
//                    chain and resolves it to the matching exercise +
//                    its threshold live, every session.
//      reps is a number, an "N-M" range string, an "Ns"/"Nmin" time
//      string, "F" (al fallo / to failure), or "mrp"/"mtp".
//
//   3. PROGRAMS
//      Each program is { id, name, weeks: [{ weekNumbers, workoutIds }] }.
//      weekNumbers groups weeks that use an identical workoutIds list;
//      workoutIds is the ordered list of workouts for that week.
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

